text: Zwartewaterland is a municipality in the province of Overijssel, the Netherlands. About 23,000 people were living there in 2021. It lies both in the region of Salland and the region of Kop van Overijssel. It was created from the former municipalities of Genemuiden, Hasselt, and Zwartsluis on 1 January 2001. == References == * Plaatsengids.nl Category:2001 establishments in the Netherlands
title: Zwartewaterland
